[36m(main_task pid=2407745)[0m <p>Query flooding is a method used in P2P networks to search for a resource, although it is not commonly used in newer versions of P2P protocols. Query flooding consists of broadcasting a search query to a large number of nodes in the network, which the nodes then forward the query to all their peers. This method was popular in early versions of the Gnutella protocol. However, it is known for its inefficiency and scalability issues. Query strings are the parameters or fields added to a base URL by a Web browser or other client applications, allowing users to specify specific details or search parameters for resource retrieval. </p>
