[36m(main_task pid=2407745)[0m Fed up with her life with Mark, a Mormon father who forces her to be more traditional, Annie decides to leave. She initially travels alone, but at the insistence of her Catholic father, she becomes the traveling companion of Susan, a devout Mormon. Together, they visit Sister Mae, an activist. Soon after, they spend the night at the home of Karena, a sexual liberation advocate and best friend of Annie's former girlfriend, Mary, where they find a dead woman's body in Karena's bathtub. Taking the body to a morgue, Annie and Susan have little success explaining their story, leading to several misunderstandings. On the way back, they are met by a character in an unfortunate relationship whom Sister Mae escorts to her rescue as the trio set up camp for the night. Meanwhile, Mark goes to Karena to tell her that he wants to see Annie, but instead meets Susan who tells him to contact Annie through the local newspaper and promises to locate her. Mark eventually locates Annie at a park with an attack dog and gains her protection, but he eventually abandons her. Upon encountering Karena once more, Mark's decision is made for him when she asks him to protect Annie. Meanwhile, one of Sister Mae's other clients, who left the rescue mission in order to go to a party, returns unexpectedly to admit that he has fallen for an attractive woman. Having seen Karena, he decides to stay with her. As a result, Annie leaves alone to continue her journey.
[36m(main_task pid=2407745)[0m Fed up with his life with Mark, Annie decided to leave, however at the insistence of his Mormon father, he had to have Susan as his travelling companion. On their journey they run into several situations, that include various misunderstanding of their religions. Their journey which was originally supposed to be for a few hours turned into an odyssey.  Then, upon meeting Sister Mae, Sister Mae asks him to take care of Annie. Mark felt forced to take care of Annie.  Susan , actually witnessed her Roman Catholicism sister kissing Karena. Therefore it's easy to let her take care of Annie. Mark then finds out that Karena had an affair with a woman. So he is forced to take the responsibility of Annie.
