[36m(main_task pid=2407745)[0m The Thrust SSC, also known as Thrust 2, was a British supersonic land vehicle developed in the 1990s. It had two versions, a car called Thrust SSC and a rocket called Thrust 2. The car reached a speed of 1,228.0 kilometres per hour (763.1 miles per hour) and the rocket reached a speed of Mach 1.011 in 1997. The car's Chief Aerodynamicist was Andy Green, who was also the driver. Andy Green was born in 1960.
