[36m(main_task pid=2407745)[0m Dave Wyndorf and Poly Styrene performed music that was influenced by different genres. Dave Wyndorf was part of the glam metal band Monster Magnet and provided guitar riffs and production for their music. The songs by Monster Magnet often had a distinctive glam rock sound, characterized by bluesy guitar riffs, synthesizers, and theatrical production. 
[36m(main_task pid=2407745)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=2407745)[0m Poly Styrene, on the other hand, was the lead singer and songwriter of the new wave punk band X-Ray Spex. The band was known for their high-energy punk music, as well as for being the first all-female group to sign with a major record label. Their sound blended punk rock with pop music elements and electronic music. X-Ray Spex also incorporated some influences from soul and funk, with their catchy hooks and energetic performances.
[36m(main_task pid=2407745)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=2407745)[0m In summary, while both Monster Magnet and X-Ray Spex were successful bands with unique sounds and genres, Dave Wyndorf's contributions were to the glam metal scene of Monster Magnet, whereas Poly Styrene's work was associated with the new wave punk and punk rock music of X-Ray Spex. Both bands, however, have been influential in their respective music scenes and have left an impact on the world of rock and pop music.
