[36m(main_task pid=2407745)[0m Psilocybin mushrooms, also known as magic mushrooms, contain various psychedelic compounds. The main compounds of interest are psilocybin, psilocin, and baeocystin. Psilocybin is the active ingredient in these mushrooms. When psilocybin enters the body, it is metabolized and converted to psilocin. This conversion process is influenced by factors such as dosage, individual factors, and the body's metabolic capabilities. Additionally, baeocystin is also a compound found in Psilocybin mushrooms, but it is not converted to psilocin.
