[36m(main_task pid=2407745)[0m The Lithuanian Order of Gediminas was granted by Grand Duke Gediminas to Voivod of Pardubitz, which was the first step towards creating a coat of arms for the Grand Duchy of Lithuania. In 1386, Grand Duke Jogaila, acting as the Grand Duke of Lithuania, commissioned a coat of arms featuring the Order of Gediminas, which was used as a symbol of the Lithuanian Republic during its formation. The Lithuanian Republic existed between 1386 and 1432, as part of the Jagiellonian Union.
